 \lim\limits_{n\to \infty} (3^n + 4^n)^{1/n} = 4. 
\alpha_1,\alpha_2,\dots,\alpha_m
A=\max\limits_{1\leq i\leq m}{\alpha_i}
A^n\leq \alpha_1^n+\cdots+\alpha_m^n\leq mA^n
A\leq (\alpha_1^n+\cdots+\alpha_m^n)^{1/n}\leq m^{1/n} A
\lim_{n\to\infty} (\alpha_1^n+\cdots+\alpha_m^n)^{1/n}=\max\limits_{1\leq i\leq m}{\alpha_i}
m^{1/n}\to 1
4^n < 3^n + 4^n < 2\cdot 4^n
=\lim_{n \to \infty} 4\left(1+\frac{3^n}{4^n}\right)^{1/n} = \lim_{n \to \infty} 4\left(1+0.75^n\right)^{1/n} = 4
